(643, '04', '05', 'Australian Sparkling Ale [BJCP 12B]', 'Pale Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.038', '1.05', '1.004', '1.006', '4.5', '6', '20', '35', '4', '7', '1', 'A well-balanced, pale, highly-carbonated, and refreshing ale suitable for drinking in a hot climate. Fairly bitter, with a moderate herbal-spicy hop and pome fruit ester profile. Smooth, neutral malt flavors with a fuller body but a crisp, highly-attenuated finish.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, pacific, traditional-style, pale-ale-family, bitter', 'Coopers Sparkling Ale', NULL),
