(645, '04', '04', 'Belgian Pale Ale [BJCP 24B]', 'Pale Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.048', '1.055', '1.01', '1.014', '4.8', '5.5', '20', '30', '8', '14', '1', 'A top-fermented, all malt, average strength Belgian ale that is moderately bitter, not dry-hopped, and without strong flavors. The copper-colored beer lacks the aggressive yeast character or sourness of many Belgian beers, but has a well-balanced, malty, fruity, and often bready and toasty profile.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, pale-ale-family, balanced', 'De Koninck Bolleke, De Ryck Special, Palm, Palm Dobble', NULL),
