(650, '06', '03', 'Double IPA [BJCP 22A]', 'IPA', 'AABC2022', '1.065', '1.085', '1.008', '1.018', '7.5', '10', '60', '100', '6', '14', '1', 'An intensely hoppy, fairly strong, bitter pale ale without the big, rich, complex maltiness, residual sweetness, and body of an American Barleywine. Strongly hopped, but clean, dry, and lacking harshness. Despite showing its strength, drinkability is an important consideration. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'very-high-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, ipa-family, bitter, hoppy', 'Columbus Brewing Bohdi, Fat Head’s Hop Juju, Port Brewing Hop-15, Russian River Pliny the Elder, Stone Ruination Double IPA 2.0, Wicked Weed Freak of Nature', NULL),
