(654, '07', '06', 'Red IPA, Specialty IPA [BJCP 21B]', 'Specialty IPA', 'AABC2022', '1.056', '1.07', '1.008', '1.016', '5.5', '7.5', '40', '70', '11', '17', '1', 'Hoppy, bitter, and moderately strong like an American IPA, but with some caramel, toffee, or fruit character as in an American Amber Ale. Retaining the dryish finish and lean body that makes IPAs so drinkable, a Red IPA is a little more flavorful and malty than an American IPA without being sweet or heavy.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, ipa-family, specialty-family, bitter, hoppy', 'Avery Hog Heaven, Cigar City Tocobaga Red IPA, Modern Times Blazing World, Tröegs Nugget Nectar', 'Entrant MUST specify a strength (session, standard, double); if no strength is specified, standard will be assumed.'),
