(657, '07', '03', 'Belgian IPA, Specialty IPA [BJCP 21B]', 'Specialty IPA', 'AABC2022', '1.058', '1.08', '1.008', '1.016', '6.2', '9.5', '50', '100', '5', '8', '1', 'A dry, hoppy IPA with fruitiness and spiciness of Belgian yeast. Often lighter in color and more attenuated, similar to a Belgian Tripel that has been brewed with more hops.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, ipa-family, specialty-family, bitter, hoppy', 'Brewery Vivant Triomphe, Green Flash Le Freak, Houblon Chouffe, Urthel Hop It', 'Entrant MUST specify a strength (session, standard, double); if no strength is specified, standard will be assumed.'),
(658, '07', '04', 'Black IPA, Specialty IPA [BJCP 21B]', 'Specialty IPA', 'AABC2022', '1.05', '1.085', '1.01', '1.018', '5.5', '9', '50', '90', '25', '40', '1', 'A beer with the dryness, hop-forward balance, and flavor characteristics of an American IPA, but darker in color. Darker malts add a gentle and supportive flavor, not a strongly roasted or burnt character.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, ipa-family, specialty-family, bitter, hoppy', '21st Amendment Back in Black, Duck-Rabbit Hoppy Bunny ABA, Stone Sublimely Self-Righteous Black IPA', 'Entrant MUST specify a strength (session, standard, double); if no strength is specified, standard will be assumed.'),
(659, '08', '01', 'Best Bitter [BJCP 11B]', 'Amber Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.04', '1.048', '1.008', '1.012', '3.8', '4.6', '25', '40', '8', '16', '1', 'A flavorful, yet refreshing, session beer. Some examples can be more malt balanced, but this should not override the overall bitter impression. Drinkability is a critical component of the style.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, amber-ale-family, bitter', 'Adnams Southwold Bitter, Fuller’s London Pride, Harvey’s Sussex Best Bitter, Salopian Darwin’s Origin, Surrey Hills Shere Drop, Timothy Taylor Landlord', NULL),
(660, '08', '03', 'Altbier [BJCP 7B]', 'Amber Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.044', '1.052', '1.008', '1.014', '4.3', '5.5', '25', '50', '9', '17', '1', 'A moderately colored, well-attenuated, bitter beer with a rich maltiness balancing a strong bitterness. Light and spicy hop character complements the malt. A dry beer with a firm body and smooth palate.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, lagered, central-europe, traditional-style, amber-ale-family, bitter', 'Bolten Alt, Diebels Alt, Füchschen Alt, Original Schlüssel Alt, Schlösser Alt, Schumacher Alt, Uerige Altbier', NULL),
(661, '08', '04', 'California Common [BJCP 19B]', 'Amber Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.048', '1.054', '1.011', '1.014', '4.5', '5.5', '30', '45', '9', '14', '1', 'A toasty and caramelly, fairly bitter, standard-strength beer with an interesting fruitiness and rustic, woody hop character. Smooth and well carbonated.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, bottom-fermented, north-america, traditional-style, amber-lager-family, bitter, hoppy', 'Anchor Steam, Steamworks Steam Engine Lager', NULL),
(662, '08', '02', 'American Amber Ale [BJCP 19A]', 'Amber Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.045', '1.06', '1.01', '1.015', '4.5', '6.2', '25', '40', '10', '17', '1', 'An amber, hoppy, moderate-strength American craft beer with a malty caramel flavor. The balance can vary quite a bit, with some versions being fairly malty and others being aggressively hoppy. Hoppy and bitter versions should not have clashing flavors with the caramel malt profile.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, amber-ale-family, balanced, hoppy', 'Anderson Valley Boont Amber Ale, Bell’s Amber Ale, Full Sail Amber, North Coast Red Seal Ale, Saint Arnold Amber Ale, Tröegs Hopback Amber Ale', NULL),
(663, '08', '05', 'Strong Bitter [BJCP 11C]', 'Amber Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.048', '1.06', '1.01', '1.016', '4.6', '6.2', '30', '50', '8', '18', '1', 'An average-strength to moderately-strong British bitter ale. The balance may vary between fairly even between malt and hops to somewhat bitter. Drinkability is a critical component of the style. A rather broad style that allows for considerable interpretation by the brewer.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'session-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, amber-ale-family, bitter', 'Bass Ale, Bateman’s Triple XB, Robinsons Trooper, Samuel Smith’s Organic Pale Ale, Shepherd Neame Bishop\'s Finger, Summit Extra Pale Ale', NULL),
(664, '09', '01', 'Irish Red Ale [BJCP 15A]', 'Brown Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.036', '1.046', '1.01', '1.014', '3.8', '5', '18', '28', '9', '14', '1', 'An easy-drinking pint, often with subtle flavors. Slightly malty in the balance sometimes with an initial soft toffee or caramel sweetness, a slightly grainy-biscuity palate, and a touch of roasted dryness in the finish. Some versions can emphasize the caramel and sweetness more, while others will favor the grainy palate and roasted dryness.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, amber-ale-family, balanced', 'Franciscan Well Rebel Red, Kilkenny Irish Beer, Murphy’s Irish Red, O’Hara’s Irish Red Ale, Porterhouse Nitro Red Ale, Smithwick’s Irish Ale', NULL),
(665, '09', '03', 'Kentucky Common; Historical Beer [BJCP 27]', 'Brown Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.044', '1.055', '1.01', '1.018', '4', '5.5', '15', '30', '11', '20', '1', 'A clean, dry, refreshing, slightly malty dark beer with high carbonation. Mild-tasting, with light toast and caramel flavors, served very fresh as a sessionable saloon beer.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, north america,historical-style, balanced', 'Apocalypse Brew Works 1912', NULL),
(666, '09', '02', 'Scottish Export [BJCP 14C]', 'Brown Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.04', '1.06', '1.01', '1.016', '3.9', '6', '15', '30', '12', '20', '1', 'A moderate-strength, malty beer with light caramel, toast, toffee, and fruit flavors. A slight roast dryness offsets the residual sweetness in the finish, with the bitterness perceived only to keep the beer from being cloying.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, amber-ale-family, malty', 'Belhaven Scottish Ale, Broughton Wee Jock 80 Shilling, Caledonian Edinburgh Castle, McEwan’s 80/-, McEwan’s Export, Traquair Bear Ale', NULL),
(667, '09', '04', 'British Brown Ale [BJCP 13B]', 'Brown Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.04', '1.052', '1.008', '1.013', '4.2', '5.9', '20', '30', '12', '22', '1', 'A malty, caramelly, brown British ale without the roasted flavors of a Porter. Balanced and flavorful, but usually a little stronger than most average UK beers.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, brown-ale-family, malty', 'AleSmith Nut Brown Ale, Cigar City Maduro Brown Ale, Maxim Double Maxim, Newcastle Brown Ale, Riggwelter Yorkshire Ale, Samuel Smith’s Nut Brown Ale', NULL),
(668, '09', '05', 'American Brown Ale [BJCP 19C]', 'Brown Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.045', '1.06', '1.01', '1.016', '4.3', '6.2', '20', '30', '18', '35', '1', 'A malty but hoppy standard-strength American ale frequently with chocolate and caramel flavors. The hop flavor and aroma complement and enhance the malt rather than clashing with it.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, brown-ale-family, balanced, hoppy', 'Avery Ellie’s Brown Ale, Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale, Brooklyn Brown Ale, Bell’s Best Brown, Smuttynose Old Brown Dog Ale, Telluride Face Down Brown', NULL),
(669, '10', '01', 'English Porter [BJCP 13C]', 'Porter', 'AABC2022', '1.04', '1.052', '1.008', '1.014', '4', '5.4', '18', '35', '20', '30', '1', 'A moderate-strength dark brown English ale with a restrained roasty, bitter character. May have a range of roasted flavors, generally without burnt qualities, and often has a malty chocolate and caramel profile.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, porter-family, malty, roasty', 'Bateman’s Salem Porter, Burton Bridge Burton Porter, Fuller’s London Porter, Nethergate Old Growler Porter, RCH Old Slug Porter, Samuel Smith Taddy Porter', NULL),
(670, '10', '02', 'Pre-Prohibition Porter; Historical Beer [BJCP 27]', 'Porter', 'AABC2022', '1.046', '1.06', '1.01', '1.016', '4.5', '6', '20', '30', '20', '30', '1', 'A historical American adaptation of English Porter by German immigrants using American ingredients, including adjuncts.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, dark-color, any-fermentation, northamerica, historical-style, porter-family, malty', 'Stegmaier Porter, Yuengling Porter', NULL),
(671, '10', '03', 'American Porter [BJCP 20A]', 'Porter', 'AABC2022', '1.05', '1.07', '1.012', '1.018', '4.8', '6.5', '25', '50', '22', '40', '1', 'A malty, bitter, and often somewhat hoppy dark beer with a balanced, roasted, and frequently chocolatey character.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, porter-family, bitter, roasty, hoppy', 'Anchor Porter, Bell’s Porter, Deschutes Black Butte Porter, Great Lakes Edmund Fitzgerald Porter, Sierra Nevada Porter, Smuttynose Robust Porter', NULL),
(672, '10', '04', 'Baltic Porter [BJCP 9C]', 'Porter', 'AABC2022', '1.06', '1.09', '1.016', '1.024', '6.5', '9.5', '20', '40', '17', '30', '1', 'A strong, dark, malty beer with different interpretations within the Baltic region. Smooth, warming, and richly malty, with complex dark fruit flavors and a roasted flavor without burnt notes.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, dark-color, any-fermentation, lagered, eastern-europe, traditional-style, porter-family, malty', 'Aldaris Mežpils Porteris, Baltika 6 Porter, Devils Backbone Danzig, Okocim Mistrzowski Porter, Sinebrychoff Porter, Zywiec Porter', NULL),
(673, '11', '01', 'Sweet Stout [BJCP 16A]', 'Stout', 'AABC2022', '1.044', '1.06', '1.012', '1.024', '4', '6', '20', '40', '30', '40', '1', 'A very dark, sweet, full-bodied, slightly roasty stout that can suggest coffee-and-cream, or sweetened espresso.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, stout-family, malty, roasty, sweet', 'Bristol Beer Factory Milk Stout, Firestone Nitro Merlin Milk Stout, Left Hand Milk Stout, Lancaster Milk Stout, Mackeson’s XXX Stout, Marston’s Pearl Jet Stout', NULL),
(674, '11', '02', 'Irish Stout [BJCP 15B]', 'Stout', 'AABC2022', '1.036', '1.044', '1.007', '1.011', '3.8', '5', '25', '45', '25', '40', '1', 'A black beer with a pronounced roasted flavor, often similar to coffee. The balance can range from fairly even to quite bitter, with the more balanced versions having a little malty sweetness and the bitter versions being quite dry. Draught versions typically are creamy from a nitro pour, but bottled versions will not have this dispense-derived character. The roasted flavor can range from dry and coffee-like to somewhat chocolaty. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, stout-family, bitter, roasty', 'Beamish Irish Stout, Belhaven Black Stout, Guinness Draught, Murphy’s Irish Stout, O’Hara’s Irish Stout, Porterhouse Irish Stout', NULL),
(675, '11', '03', 'Oatmeal Stout [BJCP 16B]', 'Stout', 'AABC2022', '1.045', '1.065', '1.01', '1.018', '4.2', '5.9', '25', '40', '22', '40', '1', 'A dark, roasty, full-bodied stout with enough sweetness to support the oat backbone. The sweetness, balance, and oatmeal impression can vary considerably.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, stout-family, balanced, roasty', 'Anderson Valley Barney Flats Oatmeal Stout, Broughton Stout Jock, St-Ambroise Oatmeal Stout, Samuel Smith Oatmeal Stout, Summit Oatmeal Stout, Young’s London Stout', NULL),
(676, '11', '04', 'Irish Extra Stout [BJCP 15C]', 'Stout', 'AABC2022', '1.052', '1.062', '1.01', '1.014', '5', '6.5', '35', '50', '30', '40', '1', 'A fuller-bodied black beer with a pronounced roasted flavor, often similar to coffee and dark chocolate with some malty complexity. The balance can range from moderately bittersweet to bitter, with the more balanced versions having up to moderate malty richness and the bitter versions being quite dry.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, stout-family, bitter, roasty', 'Guinness Extra Stout, O’Hara’s Leann Folláin, Porterhouse XXXX, Sheaf Stout', NULL),
(677, '12', '01', 'Tropical Stout [BJCP 16C]', 'Strong Stout', 'AABC2022', '1.056', '1.075', '1.01', '1.018', '5.5', '8', '30', '50', '30', '40', '1', 'A very dark, sweet, fruity, moderately strong stout with smooth, roasty flavors, yet no burnt harshness.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, stout-family, malty, roasty, sweet', 'Coopers Best Extra Stout, Guinness Foreign Extra Stout, The Kernel Export Stout London 1890, La Cumbre Malpais Stout, Pelican Tsunami Export Stout, Ridgeway Foreign Export Stout', NULL),
(678, '12', '02', 'Foreign Extra Stout [BJCP 16D]', 'Strong Stout', 'AABC2022', '1.056', '1.075', '1.01', '1.018', '6.5', '8', '50', '70', '30', '40', '1', 'A very dark, moderately strong, fairly dry, stout with prominent roast flavors.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, stout-family, balanced, roasty', 'Guinness Foreign Extra Stout, Ridgeway Foreign Export Stout, Coopers Best Extra Stout, Elysian Dragonstooth Stout.', NULL),
(679, '12', '03', 'American Stout [BJCP 20B]', 'Strong Stout', 'AABC2022', '1.05', '1.075', '1.01', '1.022', '5', '7', '35', '75', '30', '40', '1', 'A fairly strong, highly roasted, bitter, hoppy dark stout. The body and dark flavors typical of stouts with a more aggressive American hop character and bitterness.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, stout-family, bitter, roasty, hoppy', 'Avery Out of Bounds Stout, Bell’s Kalamazoo Stout, Deschutes Obsidian Stout, Sierra Nevada Stout, Trillium Secret Stairs', NULL),
(680, '12', '04', 'Imperial Stout [BJCP 20C]', 'Strong Stout', 'AABC2022', '1.075', '1.115', '1.018', '1.03', '8', '12', '50', '90', '30', '40', '1', 'An intensely-flavored, very strong, very dark stout with a broad range of interpretations. Roasty-burnt malt with a depth of dark or dried fruit flavors, and a warming, bittersweet finish. Despite the intense flavors, the components need to meld together to create a complex, harmonious beer, not a hot mess ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'very-high-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, british-isles, north-america, traditional-style, craft-style, stout-family, malty, bitter, roasty', 'American – Bell’s Expedition Stout, Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout, North Coast Old Rasputin Imperial Stout, Oskar Blues Ten Fidy, Sierra Nevada Narwhal Imperial Stout; English – 2SP Brewing Co The Russian, Courage Imperial Russian Stout, Le Coq Imperial Extra Double Stout, Samuel Smith Imperial Stout, Thornbridge Saint Petersburg', NULL);
INSERT INTO `baseline_styles` (`id`, `brewStyleGroup`, `brewStyleNum`, `brewStyle`, `brewStyleCategory`, `brewStyleVersion`, `brewStyleOG`, `brewStyleOGMax`, `brewStyleFG`, `brewStyleFGMax`, `brewStyleABV`, `brewStyleABVMax`, `brewStyleIBU`, `brewStyleIBUMax`, `brewStyleSRM`, `brewStyleSRMMax`, `brewStyleType`, `brewStyleInfo`, `brewStyleLink`, `brewStyleActive`, `brewStyleOwn`, `brewStyleReqSpec`, `brewStyleStrength`, `brewStyleCarb`, `brewStyleSweet`, `brewStyleTags`, `brewStyleComEx`, `brewStyleEntry`) VALUES
(681, '13', '03', 'American Wheat Beer [BJCP 1D]', 'Wheat & Rye Beer', 'AABC2022', '1.04', '1.055', '1.008', '1.013', '4', '5.5', '15', '30', '3', '6', '1', 'A pale, refreshing grainy, doughy, or bready wheat beer with a clean fermentation profile and a variable hop character and bitterness. Its lighter body and higher carbonation contribute to its easy-drinking nature.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, any-fermentation, north-america, craft-style, wheat-beer-family, balanced', 'Bell’s Oberon, Boulevard Unfiltered Wheat Beer, GoodLife Sweet As! Pacific Ale, Goose Island 312 Urban Wheat Ale, Widmer Hefeweizen', NULL),
(682, '13', '01', 'Weissbier [BJCP 10A]', 'Wheat & Rye Beer', 'AABC2022', '1.044', '1.053', '1.008', '1.014', '4.3', '5.6', '8', '16', '2', '6', '1', 'A pale, refreshing, lightly-hopped German wheat beer with high carbonation, dry finish, fluffy mouthfeel, and a distinctive banana-and-clove weizen yeast fermentation profile.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, central-europe, traditional-style, wheat-beer-family, malty', 'Ayinger Bräuweisse, Distelhäuser Hell Weizen, Hacker-Pschorr Hefeweißbier, Hofbräuhaus Münchner Weisse, Schneider Weisse Original Weissbier, Weihenstephaner Hefeweißbier', NULL),
(683, '13', '02', 'Witbier [BJCP 24A]', 'Wheat & Rye Beer', 'AABC2022', '1.044', '1.052', '1.008', '1.012', '4.5', '5.5', '8', '20', '2', '4', '1', 'A pale, hazy Belgian wheat beer with spices accentuating the yeast character. A delicate, lightly spiced, moderate-strength ale that is a refreshing summer drink with its high carbonation, dry finish, and light hopping.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, wheat-beer-family, spice', 'Allagash White, Blanche de Bruxelles, Celis White, Hoegaarden White, Ommegang Witte, St. Bernardus Wit', NULL),
(684, '13', '05', 'Dunkles Weissbier [BJCP 10B]', 'Wheat & Rye Beer', 'AABC2022', '1.044', '1.057', '1.008', '1.014', '4.3', '5.6', '10', '18', '14', '23', '1', 'A moderately dark German wheat beer with a distinctive banana-and-clove weizen yeast fermentation profile, supported by a toasted bread or caramel malt flavor. Highly carbonated and refreshing, with a creamy, fluffy texture and light finish.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, central-europe, traditional-style, wheat-beer-family, malty', 'Ayinger Urweisse, Ettaler Benediktiner Weißbier Dunkel, Franziskaner Hefe-Weisse Dunkel, Hirsch Dunkel Weisse, Tucher Dunkles Hefe Weizen, Weihenstephaner Hefeweißbier Dunkel', NULL),
(685, '13', '06', 'Roggenbier; Historical Beer [BJCP 27]', 'Wheat & Rye Beer', 'AABC2022', '1.046', '1.056', '1.01', '1.014', '4.5', '6', '10', '20', '14', '19', '1', 'A Dunkles Weissbier made with rye rather than wheat, but with a greater body and light finishing hops. The rye gives a bready and peppery flavor, a creamy body, and a dry, grainy finish that blends with the distinctive banana-and-clove weizen yeast character.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermenting, central-europe, historical-style, wheat-beer-family', 'Thurn und Taxis Roggen', NULL),
(686, '13', '07', 'Weizenbock [BJCP 10C]', 'Wheat & Rye Beer', 'AABC2022', '1.064', '1.09', '1.015', '1.022', '6.5', '9', '15', '30', '6', '25', '1', 'A strong and malty German wheat beer combining the best wheat and yeast flavors of a Weissbier with the rich maltiness, strength, and body of a Bock. The style range includes Bock and Doppelbock strength, with variations for pale and dark color.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, pale-color, top-fermented, central-europe, traditional-style, wheat-beer-family, malty', 'Dark – Plank Bavarian Dunkler Weizenbock, Penn Weizenbock, Schalchner Weisser Bock, Schneider Weisse Aventinus; Pale –Ayinger Weizenbock, Distelhäuser Weizen Bock, Ladenburger Weizenbock Hell, Weihenstephaner Vitus', 'The entrant MUST specify whether the entry is a pale or a dark variant.'),
(687, '13', '08', 'Wheatwine [BJCP 22D]', 'Wheat & Rye Beer', 'AABC2022', '1.08', '1.12', '1.016', '1.03', '8', '12', '30', '60', '6', '14', '1', 'A richly textured, high alcohol sipping beer with a significant grainy, bready flavor, and a sleek body. The emphasis is first on the bready, wheaty flavors with malt, hops, fruity yeast, and alcohol complexity.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'very-high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, strong-ale-family, wheat-beer-family, balanced, hoppy', 'The Bruery White Oak, Castelain Winter Ale, Perennial Heart of Gold, Two Brothers Bare Tree', NULL),
(688, '13', '04', 'Lichtenhainer; Historical Beer [BJCP 27]', 'Wheat & Rye Beer', 'AABC2022', '1.032', '1.04', '1.004', '1.008', '3.5', '4.7', '5', '12', '3', '6', '1', 'A sour, smoked, lower-gravity historical central European wheat beer. Complex yet refreshing character due to high attenuation and carbonation, along with low bitterness and moderate sourness. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, centraleurope, historical-style, wheat-beer-family, sour, smoke', 'Live Oak Lichtenhainer, Wöllnitzer Weissbier', NULL),
(689, '14', '01', 'Saison [BJCP 25B]', 'Belgian Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.048', '1.065', '1.002', '1.008', '3.5', '9.5', '20', '35', '5', '22', '1', 'A family of refreshing, highly attenuated, hoppy, and fairly bitter Belgian ales with a very dry finish and high carbonation. Characterized by a fruity, spicy, sometimes phenolic fermentation profile, and the use of cereal grains and sometimes spices for complexity. Several variations in strength and color exist.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, bitter', 'Ellezelloise Saison, Fanome Saison, Lefebvre Saison 1900, Saison Dupont Vieille Provision, Saison de Pipaix, Saison Regal, Saison Voisin, Boulevard Tank 7 Farmhouse Ale.', 'The entrant MUST specify the strength (table, standard, super) and the color (pale, dark). The entrant MAY identify character grains used. '),
(690, '14', '04', 'Belgian Single [BJCP 26A]', 'Belgian Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.044', '1.054', '1.004', '1.01', '4.8', '6', '25', '45', '3', '5', '1', 'A blond, bitter, hoppy table beer that is very dry and highly carbonated. The aggressive fruity-spicy Belgian yeast character and high bitterness is forward in the balance, with a soft, supportive grainy-sweet malt palate, and a spicy-floral hop profile. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, top-fermenting, western-europe, craft-style, bitter, hoppy', 'Chimay Gold, La Trappe Puur, Russian River Redemption, St. Bernardus Extra 4, Westmalle Extra, Westvleteren Blond', NULL),
(691, '14', '02', 'Bière de Garde [BJCP 24C]', 'Belgian Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.06', '1.08', '1.008', '1.016', '6', '8.5', '18', '28', '6', '19', '1', 'A family of smooth, fairly strong, malty, lagered artisanal French beer with a range of malt flavors appropriate for the blond, amber, or brown color. All are malty yet dry, with clean flavors. Darker versions have more malt character, while paler versions can have more hops while still remaining malt-focused beers.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, pale-color, amber-color, any-fermentation, lagered, western-europe, traditional-style, amber-ale-family, malty', 'Ch’Ti Blonde, Jenlain Ambrée, La Choulette Brune, Russian River Perdition, Saint Sylvestre 3 Monts Blonde, Two Brothers Domaine Dupage', 'Entrant MUST specify blond, amber, or brown Bière de Garde.'),
(692, '14', '03', 'Belgian Dubbel [BJCP 26B]', 'Belgian Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.062', '1.075', '1.008', '1.018', '6', '7.6', '15', '25', '10', '17', '1', 'A deep reddish-copper, moderately strong, malty, complex Belgian ale with rich malty flavors, dark or dried fruit esters, and light alcohol blended together in a malty presentation that still finishes fairly dry.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, malty', 'Chimay Red, Corsendonk Bruin, La Trappe Dubbel, Rochefort 6, St. Bernardus Pater 6, Westmalle Dubbel', NULL),
(693, '14', '05', 'Belgian Tripel [BJCP 26C]', 'Belgian Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.075', '1.085', '1.008', '1.014', '7.5', '9.5', '20', '40', '4.5', '7', '1', 'A strong, pale, somewhat spicy Belgian ale with a pleasant rounded malt flavor, firm bitterness, and dry finish. Quite aromatic, with spicy, fruity, and light alcohol notes combining with the supportive clean malt character to produce a surprisingly drinkable beverage considering the high alcohol content.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, bitter', 'Chimay Tripel, La Rulles Tripel, La Trappe Tripel, St. Bernardus Tripel, Val-Dieu Triple, Westmalle Tripel', NULL),
(694, '14', '06', 'Belgian Golden Strong Ale [BJCP 25C]', 'Belgian Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.07', '1.095', '1.005', '1.016', '7.5', '10.5', '22', '35', '3', '6', '1', 'A very pale, highly attenuated, strong Belgian ale that is more fruity and hoppy than spicy. Complex and delicate, the dry finish, light body, and high carbonation accentuate the yeast and hop character. Sparkling carbonation and effervescent, forming a rocky white head.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'very-high-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, bitter', 'Brigand, Delirium Tremens, Duvel, Judas, Lucifer, Russian River Damnation', NULL),
(695, '14', '07', 'Belgian Dark Strong Ale [BJCP 26D]', 'Belgian Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.075', '1.11', '1.01', '1.024', '8', '11', '20', '35', '12', '22', '1', 'A dark, complex, very strong Belgian ale with a delicious blend of malt richness, dark fruit flavors, and spicy notes. Complex, rich, smooth, and dangerous.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'very-high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, malty', 'Achel Extra Bruin, Boulevard The Sixth Glass, Chimay Blue, Rochefort 10, St. Bernardus Abt 12, Westvleteren 12', NULL),
(696, '15', '01', 'Helles Bock [BJCP 4C]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.064', '1.072', '1.011', '1.008', '6.3', '7.4', '23', '35', '6', '9', '1', 'A relatively pale, strong, malty German lager with a nicely attenuated finish that enhances drinkability. The hop character is generally more apparent and the malt character less deeply rich than in other Bocks.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, pale-color, bottom-fermented, lagered, central-europe, traditional-style, bock-family, malty', 'Altenmünster Maibock, Ayinger Maibock, Chuckanut Maibock, Einbecker Mai-Ur-Bock, Hofbräu Maibock, Mahr’s Heller Bock', NULL),
(697, '15', '06', 'British Strong Ale [BJCP 17A]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.055', '1.08', '1.015', '1.022', '5.5', '8', '30', '60', '8', '22', '1', 'An ale of respectable alcoholic strength, traditionally bottled-conditioned and cellared. Can have a wide range of interpretations, but most will have varying degrees of malty richness, late hops and bitterness, fruity esters, and alcohol warmth. The malt and adjunct flavors and intensity can vary widely, but any combination should result in an agreeable palate experience.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, strong-ale-family, malty', 'Fuller’s 1845, Harvey’s Elizabethan Ale, J.W. Lees Moonraker, McEwan’s Champion, Samuel Smith’s Winter Welcome, Shepherd Neame 1698', NULL),
(698, '15', '07', 'Old Ale [BJCP 17B]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.055', '1.088', '1.015', '1.022', '5.5', '9', '30', '60', '10', '22', '1', 'A stronger-than-average English ale, though usually not as strong or rich as an English Barley Wine, but usually malty. Warming. Shows positive maturation effects of a well-kept, aged beer.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, strong-ale-family, malty, aged', 'Avery Old Jubilation, Berlina Old Ale, Greene King Strong Suffolk Ale, Marston Owd Roger, Theakston Old Peculier', NULL),
(699, '15', '02', 'Dunkles Bock [BJCP 6C]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.054', '1.072', '0.013', '1.019', '6.3', '7.2', '20', '27', '14', '22', '1', 'A strong, dark, malty German lager beer that emphasizes the malty-rich and somewhat toasty qualities of continental malts without being sweet in the finish.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, bottom-fermented, lagered, central-europe, traditional-style, bock-family, malty', 'Aass Bock, Einbecker Ur-Bock Dunkel, Kneitinger Bock, Lindeboom Bock, Schell’s Bock, Penn Brewery St. Nikolaus Bock', NULL),
(700, '15', '03', 'Doppelbock [BJCP 9A]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.072', '1.112', '1.016', '1.024', '7', '10', '16', '26', '6', '25', '1', 'A strong, rich, and very malty German lager that can have both pale and dark variants. The darker versions have more richly-developed, deeper malt flavors, while the paler versions have slightly more hops and dryness.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, pale-color, bottom-fermented, lagered, central-europe, traditional-style, bock-family, malty', 'Dark Versions - Andechs Doppelbock Dunkel, Ayinger Celebrator, Paulaner Salvator, Spaten Optimator, Tröegs Troegenator, Weihenstephaner Korbinian; Pale Versions - Eggenberg Urbock 23º, Meinel Doppelbock Hell, Plank Bavarian Heller Doppelbock, Riegele Auris 19, Schönbuch Doppelbock Hell, Staffelberg-Bräu Zwergator', 'The entrant select specify whether the entry is a pale or a dark variant.'),
(701, '15', '05', 'Wee Heavy [BJCP 17C]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.07', '1.013', '1.018', '1.04', '6.5', '10', '17', '35', '14', '25', '1', 'Rich, sweet malt depth with caramel, toffee, and fruity flavors. Full-bodied and chewy, with warming alcohol. Restrained bitterness, but not cloying or syrupy.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, strong-ale-family, malty', 'Belhaven Wee Heavy, Broughton Old Jock, McEwan’s Scotch Ale, Orkney Skull Splitter, Traquair House Ale, The Duck-Rabbit Wee Heavy Scotch-Style Ale', NULL),
(702, '15', '08', 'English Barleywine [BJCP 17D]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.08', '1.12', '1.018', '1.03', '8', '12', '35', '70', '8', '22', '1', 'A strong and richly malty ale with a pleasant fruity or hoppy depth. A wintertime sipper with a full, chewy body and warming alcohol.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'very-high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, british-isles, traditional-style, strong-ale-family, malty', 'Burton Bridge Thomas Sykes Old Ale, Coniston No. 9 Barley Wine, Fuller’s Golden Pride, Hogs Back A over T, J.W. Lee’s Vintage Harvest Ale, Robinson’s Old Tom', NULL),
(703, '15', '04', 'Eisbock [BJCP 9B]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.078', '1.12', '1.02', '1.035', '9', '14', '25', '35', '17', '30', '1', 'A strong, full-bodied, rich, and malty dark German lager often with a viscous quality and strong flavors. Even though flavors are concentrated, the alcohol should be smooth and warming, not burning. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'very-high-strength, amber-color, bottom-fermented, lagered, central-europe, traditional-style, bock-family, malty', 'Kulmbacher Eisbock', NULL),
(704, '15', '11', 'Sahti; Historical Beer [BJCP 27]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.076', '1.12', '1.016', '1.038', '7', '11', '0', '15', '4', '22', '1', 'A sweet, heavy, strong traditional Finnish farmhouse beer usually with rye and juniper, and a banana-clove yeast character.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, centraleurope, historical-style, spice', 'Now made year-round by several breweries in Finland.', NULL),
(705, '15', '09', 'American Strong Ale [BJCP 22B]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.062', '1.09', '1.014', '1.024', '6.3', '10', '50', '100', '7', '18', '1', 'A malty, bitter, and strong American Ale fitting in the space between American Barleywine, Double IPA, and Red IPA. The malty and hoppy flavors can be quite strong, but are generally in balance. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, strong-ale-family, bitter, hoppy', 'Arrogant Bastard Ale, Fat Head’s Bone Head, Great Lakes Nosferatu, Oskar Blues G’Knight, Port Brewing Shark Attack Double Red Ale', NULL),
(706, '15', '10', 'American Barleywine [BJCP 22C]', 'Strong Ale & Lager', 'AABC2022', '1.08', '1.12', '1.016', '1.03', '8', '12', '50', '100', '9', '18', '1', 'A very strong, malty, hoppy, bitter American ale with a rich palate, full mouthfeel, and warming aftertaste, suitable for contemplative sipping.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'very-high-strength, amber-color, top-fermented, north-america, craft-style, strong-ale-family, bitter, hoppy', 'Anchor Old Foghorn, Bell’s Third Coast Old Ale, East End Gratitude, Hair of the Dog Doggie Claws, Sierra Nevada Bigfoot', NULL),
(707, '16', '01', 'Gose [BJCP 23G]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.036', '1.056', '1.006', '1.01', '4.2', '4.8', '5', '12', '3', '4', '1', 'A tart, lightly-bittered historical central European wheat beer with a distinctive but restrained salt and coriander character. Very refreshing, with a dry finish, high carbonation, and bright flavors.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, top-fermented, centraleurope, historical-style, wheat-beer-family, sour, spice', 'Anderson Valley Gose, Bayerisch Bahnhof Leipziger Gose, Original Ritterguts Gose, Westbrook Gose', NULL),
(708, '16', '05', 'Straight Sour Beer [BJCP 28D]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.048', '1.065', '1.006', '1.013', '4.5', '7', '3', '8', '2', '3', '1', 'A pale, refreshing, sour beer with a clean lactic sourness. A gentle, pale malt flavor supports the lemony sourness with moderate fruity esters. Intended for beers fermented with Sacch and Lacto, with or without oak aging, produced using any technique (e.g., traditional co-fermentation, quick kettle souring).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'pale-color, top-fermented, sour', 'Rarely found, as this style is typically the base for other Specialty-Type Beers.', NULL),
(709, '16', '02', 'Lambic [BJCP 23D]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.04', '1.054', '1.001', '1.01', '5', '6.5', '0', '10', '3', '6', '1', 'A fairly sour, often moderately funky, wild Belgian wheat beer with sourness taking the place of hop bitterness in the balance. Traditionally served uncarbonated as a caf', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, wild-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, wheat-beer-family, sour', 'Cantillon Grand Cru Bruocsella. In the Brussels area, many specialty cafés have draught lambic from Boon, De Cam, Cantillon, Drie Fonteinen, Lindemans, Timmermans, Girardin and others.', NULL),
(710, '16', '03', 'Gueuze [BJCP 23E]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.04', '1.054', '1', '1.006', '5', '8', '0', '10', '5', '6', '1', 'A very refreshing, highly carbonated, pleasantly sour but balanced wild Belgian wheat beer. The wild beer character can be complex and varied, combining sour, funky, and fruity flavors.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'high-strength, pale-color, wild-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, wheat-beer-family, aged, sour', '3 Fonteinen Oud Gueuze, Cantillon Classic Gueuze 100% Lambic, Girardin Gueuze 1882 (Black label), Hanssens Oude Gueuze, Lindemans Gueuze Cuvée René, Oude Gueuze Boon', NULL),
(711, '16', '04', 'Fruit Lambic [BJCP 23F]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.04', '1.06', '1', '1.006', '5', '7', '0', '10', '3', '7', '1', 'A complex, refreshing, pleasantly sour Belgian wheat beer blending a complementary fermented fruit character with a sour, funky Gueuze. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, pale-color, wild-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, wheat-beer-family, sour, fruit', '3 Fonteinen Schaerbeekse Kriek, Cantillon Fou’ Foune, Cantillon Lou Pepe Framboise, Cantillon Vigneronne, Hanssens Oude Kriek, Oude Kriek Boon', 'The type of fruit used MUST be specified. The brewer must declare a carbonation level (low, medium, high) and a sweetness level (low/none, medium, high).'),
(712, '16', '06', 'Flanders Red Ale [BJCP 23B]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.048', '1.057', '1.002', '1.012', '4.6', '6.5', '10', '25', '10', '17', '1', 'A sour and fruity oak-aged reddish-brown Belgian-style ale with supportive toasty malt flavors and fruit complexity. The dry, tannic finish supports the suggestion of a vintage red wine.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, amber-color, top-fermenting, western-europe, traditional-style, sour-ale-family, balanced, sour, wood', 'Cuvée des Jacobins, Duchesse de Bourgogne, New Belgium La Folie, Rodenbach Classic, Rodenbach Grand Cru, Vichtenaar Flemish Ale', NULL),
(713, '16', '07', 'Oud Bruin [BJCP 23C]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '1.04', '1.074', '1.008', '1.012', '4', '8', '20', '25', '17', '22', '1', 'A malty, fruity, aged, somewhat sour Belgian-style brown ale with a caramel-chocolate malt flavor, and often substantial alcohol.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'standard-strength, dark-color, top-fermented, western-europe, traditional-style, sour-ale-family, malty, sour', 'Ichtegem Oud Bruin, Liefmans Goudenband, Liefmans Oud Bruin, Petrus Roodbruin, pFriem Oud Bruin, VanderGhinste Roodbruin', NULL),
(714, '16', '08', 'Brett Beer [BJCP 28A]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'Most often drier and fruitier than the base style suggests. Fruity or funky notes range from low to high, depending on the age of the beer and strains of Brett used. May possess a light non-lactic acidity. Intended for beer with or without oak aging that has been fermented with Sacch and Brett, or with Brett only.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'wild-fermentation, north-america, craft-style, specialty-beer', 'Boulevard Saison Brett, Hill Farmstead Arthur, Logsdon Seizoen Bretta, Lost Abbey Brett Devo, Russian River Sanctification, The Bruery Saison Rue', 'The entrant MUST specify either a Base Style, or provide a description of the ingredients, specs, or desired character. The entrant MAY specify the strains of Brett used.'),
(715, '16', '09', 'Mixed-Fermentation Sour Beer [BJCP 28B]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A sour and funky version of a base style of beer. Intended for beer fermented with any combination of Sacch, Lacto, Pedio, and Brett (or additional yeast or bacteria), with or without oak aging (except if the beer fits instead in 28A or 28D).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'wild-fermentation, north-america, craft-style, specialty-beer, sour', 'Boulevard Love Child, Jester King Le Petit Prince, Jolly Pumpkin Oro de Calabaza, Lost Abbey Ghosts in the Forest, New Belgium Le Terroir, Russian River Temptation', 'The entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying yeast or bacteria used and either a Base Style, or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer.'),
(716, '16', '10', 'Wild Specialty Beer [BJCP 28C]', 'Sour & Wild Ale', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'An American Wild Ale with fruit, herbs, spices, or other Specialty-Type Ingredients. Intended for variations of a Base Style beer from style 28A, 28B, or 28D. These variations may include the addition of one or more Specialty-Type Ingredients; aging in non-traditional wood varieties that impart a significant and identifiable wood character (e.g., Spanish Cedar, Amburana); or aging in barrels previously containing another alcohol (e.g., spirits, wine, cider).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'wild-fermentation, north-america, craft-style, specialty-beer, sour, fruit', 'Cascade Bourbonic Plague, Jester King Atrial Rubicite, New Belgium Dominga Mimosa Sour, New Glarus Wisconsin Belgian Red, Russian River Supplication, The Lost Abbey Cuvee de Tomme', 'Entrant MUST specify any Specialty-Type Ingredient (e.g., fruit, spice, herb, or wood) used. Entrant MUST specify either a description of the beer, identifying yeast or bacteria used and either a Base Style, or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(717, '17', '01', 'Fruit Beer [BJCP 29A]', 'Fruit & Spice Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A pleasant integration of fruit with beer, but still recognizable as beer. The fruit character should be evident but in balance with the beer, not so forward as to suggest an artificial product.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, fruit', '21st Amendment Watermelon Wheat, Anderson Valley Blood Orange Gose, Avery Liliko’i Kepolo, Ballast Point Grapefruit Sculpin, Bell’s Cherry Stout, Founders Rübæus', 'The entrant MUST specify the type(s) of fruit used. Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items. Fruit Beers based on a Classic Style should be entered in this style, except Lambic '),
(718, '17', '02', 'Fruit and Spice Beer [BJCP 29B]', 'Fruit & Spice Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A tasteful union of fruit, spice, and beer, but still recognizable as beer. The fruit and spice character should each be evident but in balance with the beer, not so forward as to suggest an artificial product. Use the definitions of Fruit in the preamble to Category 29 and Spice in the preamble to Category 30; any combination of ingredients valid in Styles 29A and 30A are allowable in this category. For this style, the word ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, fruit, spice', 'Cigar City Margarita Gose, Firestone Walker Chocolate Cherry Stout, Golden Road Spicy Mango Cart, Kona Island Colada Cream Ale, New Glarus Blueberry Cocoa Stout, Sun King Orange Vanilla Sunlight', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of fruit, and the type of SHV used; individual SHV ingredients do not need to be specified if a well-known blend of spices is used (e.g., apple pie spice). Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(719, '17', '03', 'Specialty Fruit Beer [BJCP 29C]', 'Fruit & Spice Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A appealing combination of fruit, sugar, and beer, but still recognizable as a beer. The fruit and sugar character should both be evident but in balance with the beer, not so forward as to suggest an artificial product. A Specialty Fruit Beer is a Fruit Beer with some additional ingredients, such as fermentable sugars (e.g., honey, brown sugar, invert sugar), sweeteners (e.g., lactose), adjuncts, alternative grains, or other special ingredients added, or some additional process applied. A Specialty Fruit Beer can use any style within the Fruit Beer category as a base style (currently, 29A, 29B, or 29D).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, fruit', 'The Bruery Goses are Red, New Planet Raspberry Ale, Tired Hands Strawberry Milkshake IPA, WeldWerks Piña Colada IPA', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of fruit used. The entrant MUST specify the type of additional ingredient (per the introduction) or special process employed. Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(720, '17', '04', 'Grape Ale [BJCP 29D]', 'Fruit & Spice Beer', 'AABC2022', '1.059', '1.075', '1.004', '1.013', '6', '8.5', '10', '30', '4', '8', '1', 'Combines the profile of a sparkling wine and a relatively neutral base beer allowing the aromatic qualities of the grape to blend pleasantly with hop and yeast aromatics. Can be in a range from refreshing to complex.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, fruit', 'Montegioco Open Mind, Birrificio del Forte Il Tralcio, Luppolajo Mons Rubus, Firestone Walker Feral Vinifera, pFriem Family Brewers Druif, 4 Árvores Abbondanza', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of grape used. The entrant MAY provide additional information about the base style or characteristic ingredients.'),
(721, '17', '05', 'Spice, Herb, or Vegetable Beer [BJCP 30A]', 'Fruit & Spice Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'An appealing fusion of spices, herbs, or vegetables (SHVs) and beer, but still recognizable as beer. The SHV character should be evident but in balance with the beer, not so forward as to suggest an artificial product. Often called Spice Beer, regardless of whether spices, herbs, or vegetables are used.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, spice', 'Alesmith Speedway Stout, Elysian Avatar Jasmine IPA, Founders Breakfast Stout, Rogue Yellow Snow Pilsner, Traquair Jacobite Ale, Young’s Double Chocolate Stout', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of spices, herbs, or vegetables used, but individual ingredients do not need to be specified if a well-known spice blend is used (e.g., apple pie spice, curry powder, chili powder). Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(722, '17', '06', 'Autumn Seasonal Beer [BJCP 30B]', 'Fruit & Spice Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A malty, spiced beer that often has a moderately rich body and slightly warming finish suggesting a good accompaniment for the cool fall season, and often evocative of harvest or Thanksgiving traditions. Autumn Seasonal Beers are beers that suggest cool weather and the autumn harvest season, and may include pumpkins, gourds, or other squashes, and associated spices.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, spice', 'Dogfish Head Punkin Ale, Elysian Punkuccino, Rogue Pumpkin Patch Ale, Schlafly Pumpkin Ale, UFO Pumpkin, Weyerbacher Imperial Pumpkin', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of spices, herbs, or vegetables used; individual ingredients do not need to be specified if a well-known blend of spices is used (e.g., pumpkin pie spice). Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(723, '17', '07', 'Winter Seasonal Beer [BJCP 30C]', 'Fruit & Spice Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A stronger, darker, spiced beer that often has a rich body and warming finish suggesting a good accompaniment for the cold winter season. Winter Seasonal Beers are beers that suggest cold weather and the Christmas holiday season, and may include holiday spices, specialty sugars, and other products that are reminiscent of the festive season. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, spice', 'Anchor Christmas Ale, Great Lakes Christmas Ale, Harpoon Winter Warmer, Rogue Santa’s Private Reserve, Schlafly Christmas Ale, Troeg’s The Mad Elf', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of spices, sugars, fruits, or additional fermentables used; individual ingredients do not need to be specified if a well-known blend of spices is used (e.g., mulling spice). Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(724, '17', '08', 'Specialty Spice Beer [BJCP 30D]', 'Fruit & Spice Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'An appealing combination of spices, herbs, or vegetables (SHVs), sugars, and beer, but still recognizable as beer. The SHV and sugar character should both be evident but in balance with the beer, not so forward as to suggest an artificial product. A Specialty Spice Beer is a 30A Spice, Herb, or Vegetable (SHV) Beer with some additional ingredients, such as fermentable sugars (e.g., honey, brown sugar, invert sugar, maple syrup), sweeteners (e.g., lactose), adjuncts, alternative grains, or other special ingredients added, or some additional process applied. 30B Autumn and 30C Winter Seasonal Beers already allow additional ingredients, and should not be used as a base in this style.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, spice', 'New Belgium Honey Orange Tripel, Westbrook It’s Tiki Time', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of SHVs used, but individual ingredients do not need to be specified if a well-known spice blend is used (e.g., apple pie spice, curry powder, chili powder). The entrant MUST specify the type of additional ingredient (per the introduction) or special process employed. Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(725, '18', '01', 'Classic Style Smoked Beer [BJCP 32A]', 'Specialty Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A well-balanced fusion of the malt and hops of the base beer style with a pleasant and agreeable smoke character. Intended for smoked versions of Classic Style beers, except if the Classic Style beer has smoke as an inherent part of its definition (of course, that beer should be entered in its base style, such as Rauchbier).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, smoke', 'Alaskan Smoked Porter, Schlenkerla Oak Smoke Doppelbock, Schlenkerla Rauchbier Weizen, Schlenkerla Rauchbier Ur-Bock, O’Fallon Smoked Porter, Spezial Rauchbier Lagerbier', 'The entrant MUST specify a Base Style. The entrant MUST specify the type of wood or smoke if a varietal smoke character is noticeable.'),
(726, '18', '02', 'Specialty Smoked Beer [BJCP 32B]', 'Specialty Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A well-balanced fusion of the malt and hops of the base specialty beer style with a pleasant and agreeable smoke character. A Specialty Smoked Beer is either a smoked beer based on something other than a Classic Style (a Specialty-Type style, or a broad style family such as Porter rather than a specific style), OR any type of smoked beer with additional specialty ingredients (fruits, vegetables, spices) or processes employed that transform the beer into something more unique.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, smoke', 'Fat Head’s Up in Smoke, Ommegang Bourbon Barrel Vanilla Smoked Porter', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of wood or smoke if a varietal smoke character is noticeable. The entrant MUST specify the additional ingredients or processes that make this a specialty smoked beer. Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a base style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(727, '18', '03', 'Wood-Aged Beer [BJCP 33A]', 'Specialty Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A pleasant enhancement of the base beer style with the characteristics from aging in contact with wood. The best examples will be smooth, flavorful, well-balanced, and well-aged. This style is intended for beer aged in wood without added alcohol character from previous use of the barrel. Bourbon-barrel or other beers with an added alcohol character should be entered as 33B Specialty Wood-Aged Beer. This category should not be used for base styles where wood-aging is a fundamental requirement for the style (e.g., Flanders Red, Lambic). Beers made using either limited wood aging or products that only provide a subtle background character may be entered in the base beer style categories as long as the wood character isn', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, wood', 'Bush Prestige, Cigar City Spanish Cedar Jai Alai, Firestone Walker Double Barrel Ale, Midnight Sun Arctic Devil, Petrus Aged Pale, Samuel Smith Yorkshire Stingo', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of wood used and the toast or char level (if used). If an unusual varietal wood is used, the entrant MUST supply a brief description of the sensory aspects the wood adds to beer. Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(728, '18', '04', 'Specialty Wood-Aged Beer [BJCP 33B]', 'Specialty Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'An elevation of the base beer style with characteristics from aging in contact with wood, including alcoholic products previously in contact with the wood. The best examples will be smooth, flavorful, well-balanced, and well-aged. This style is intended for beer aged in wood with added alcohol character from previous use of the barrel. Bourbon-barrel or other similar beers should be entered here.  ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer, wood', 'AleSmith Barrel-Aged Old Numbskull, Founders Kentucky Breakfast Stout, Firestone Walker Parabola, Goose Island Bourbon County Stout, Great Divide Barrel Aged Yeti, The Lost Abbey Angel’s Share Ale', 'The entrant MUST specify the additional alcohol character, with information about the barrel if relevant to the finished flavor profile. If an unusual wood or ingredient has been used, the entrant MUST supply a brief description of the sensory aspects the ingredients add to the beer. Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(729, '18', '05', 'Alternative Grain Beer [BJCP 31A]', 'Specialty Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A base beer enhanced by or featuring the character of additional grains. The specific character depends greatly on the added grains. An Alternative Grain Beer is a standard beer (Classic Style or not) with additional or non-standard brewing grains (e.g., rye, oats, buckwheat, spelt, millet, sorghum, rice) added or used exclusively. Gluten-free (GF) beers made from completely gluten-free ingredients may be entered here, while GF beers using process-based gluten removal should be entered in their respective base style categories. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer', 'Blue/Point Rastafarye Ale, Green’s India Pale Ale, Lakefront New Grist, New Planet Pale Ale, Rogue Morimoto Soba Ale, Voodoo Swimming Jeans', 'he entrant MUST specify the type of alternative grain used. Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(730, '18', '06', 'Alternative Sugar Beer [BJCP 31B]', 'Specialty Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'A tasteful integration of sugar and beer, but still recognizable as beer. The sugar character should both be evident and in balance with the beer, not so forward as to suggest an artificial product. An Alternative Sugar Beer is a standard beer (Classic Style or not) with added sweeteners, including fermentable sugars (e.g., honey, brown sugar, invert sugar, molasses, treacle, maple syrup, sorghum), unfermentable sugars (e.g., lactose), sugar alcohols (e.g., sorbitol), and any other sweetener (natural or artificial) that affects the flavor profile. The beers may or may not have any residual sweetness; it depends on the type of sugar, but flavor contributions are expected.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer', 'Bell’s Hopslam, Cervejaria Colorado Appia, Fifth Hammer Break of Jawn, Groundswell Piloncillo, Long Trail Harvest, New Glarus Cabin Fever', 'The entrant MUST specify the type of sugar used. Entrant MUST specify a description of the beer, identifying either a Base Style or the ingredients, specs, or target character of the beer. A general description of the special nature of the beer can cover all the required items.'),
(731, '18', '08', 'Commercial Specialty Beer [BJCP 34A]', 'Specialty Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'This style is intended for reproductions or interpretations of specific commercial beers that don’t fit within defined styles. Beers entered here do not need to be exact copies. The beer should be judged as to how well it fits the broader style represented by the example beer, not how well it is an exact copy of a specific commercial product. If a Commercial Specialty Beer fits another defined style, do not enter it here.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer', 'Orval, La Chouffe', 'The entrant MUST specify the name of the commercial beer, specifications (vital statistics) for the beer, and either a brief sensory description or a list of ingredients used in making the beer. Without this information, judges who are unfamiliar with the beer will have no basis for comparison.'),
(732, '18', '09', 'Mixed-Style Beer [BJCP 34B]', 'Specialty Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'Based on the declared Base Styles, methods, and ingredients. As with all Specialty-Type Beers, the resulting combination of beer styles needs to be harmonious and balanced, and be pleasant to drink. This style is intended for beers in Existing Styles (previously-defined Classic Style beers or Specialty-Type Beers) that are either: 1) A combination of Existing Styles that are not defined previously in the guidelines, including combination of Specialty-Type Beers not otherwise allowable elsewhere; 2) A variation of an Existing Style using a non-traditional method or process (e.g., dry-hopping, ‘eis’-ing, stein bier) for that style. A variation of an Existing Style using a non-traditional method or process (e.g., dry-hopping, ‘eis’-ing, stein bier) for that style; 3) A variation of an Existing Style using a non-traditional ingredient (e.g., yeast with a non-traditional profile, hops with a different character than described in the Base Style); 4) Out-of-spec variations of an Existing Style (e.g., ‘imperial’ versions, ‘session’ versions, overly-sweet versions, etc.). This style is intended for beers that can’t be entered in previously-listed styles first, including (and especially) the declared Base Style of beer. However, if the unusual method, process, or ingredient results in a beer that now fits within another defined style, the beer should be entered there. Note that some styles already allow for different strengths (e.g., IPAs, Saisons), so those variations should be entered as the appropriate Base Style.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer', 'Birrificio Italiano Tipopils, Firestone Walker Pivo Pils, Jack’s Abby Hoponius Union, Ommegang Helles Superior', ' The entrant MUST specify the Base Style or Styles being used, and any special ingredients, processes, or variations involved. The entrant MAY provide an additional description of the sensory profile of the beer or the vital statistics of the resulting beer.'),
(733, '18', '07', 'Experimental Beer [BJCP 34C]', 'Specialty Beer', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'This is explicitly a catch-all category for any beer that does not fit into an Existing Style description. No beer is ever “out of style” in this style, unless it can be entered in another beer style first. This is the last resort for any beer entered into a competition. With the broad definition for previous styles, this style should be rarely used.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'specialty-beer', NULL, 'The entrant MUST specify the special nature of the experimental beer, including the special ingredients or processes that make it not fit elsewhere in the guidelines. The entrant MUST provide vital statistics for the beer, and either a brief sensory description or a list of ingredients used in making the beer. Without this information, judges will have no basis for evaluation.'),
(734, '19', '01', 'Dry Mead [BJCP M1A]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'Similar in balance, body, finish and flavor intensity to a dry white wine, with a pleasant mixture of subtle honey character, soft fruity esters, and clean alcohol. Complexity, harmony, and balance of sensory elements are most desirable, with no inconsistencies in color, aroma, flavor or aftertaste. The proper balance of sweetness, acidity, alcohol, and honey character is the essential final measure of any mead.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 1, 1, 0, '', 'White Winter Dry Mead, Sky River Dry Mead, Intermiel Bouquet Printanier.', 'Entry Instructions: Entrants MUST specify carbonation level and strength. Sweetness is assumed to be DRY in this category. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties.'),
(735, '19', '02', 'Semi-Sweet Mead [BJCP M1B]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'Similar in balance, body, finish and flavor intensity to a semisweet (or medium-dry) white wine, with a pleasant mixture of honey character, light sweetness, soft fruity esters, and clean alcohol. Complexity, harmony, and balance of sensory elements are most desirable, with no inconsistencies in color, aroma, flavor or aftertaste. The proper balance of sweetness, acidity, alcohol, and honey character is the essential final measure of any mead.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 1, 1, 0, '', 'Lurgashall English Mead, Redstone Traditional Mountain Honey Wine, Sky River Semi-Sweet Mead, Intermiel Verge d&rsquo;Or and Melilot.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level and strength. Sweetness is assumed to be SEMI-SWEET in this category. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties.'),
(736, '19', '03', 'Sweet Mead [BJCP M1C]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'Similar in balance, body, finish and flavor intensity to a well-made dessert wine (such as Sauternes), with a pleasant mixture of honey character, residual sweetness, soft fruity esters, and clean alcohol. Complexity, harmony, and balance of sensory elements are most desirable, with no inconsistencies in color, aroma, flavor or aftertaste. The proper balance of sweetness, acidity, alcohol, and honey character is the essential final measure of any mead.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 1, 1, 0, '', 'Moonlight Sensual, Lurgashall Christmas Mead, Chaucer\'s Mead, Rabbit\'s Foot Sweet Wildflower Honey Mead, Intermiel Benoite.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level and strength. Sweetness is assumed to be SWEET in this category. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties.'),
(737, '19', '04', 'Cyser [BJCP M2A]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'In well-made examples of the style, the fruit is both distinctive and well-incorporated into the honey-sweet-acid-tannin-alcohol balance of the mead. Some of the best strong examples have the taste and aroma of an aged Calvados (apple brandy from northern France), while subtle, dry versions can taste similar to many fine white wines. There should be an appealing blend of the fruit and honey character but not necessarily an even balance. Generally a good tannin-sweetness balance is desired, though very dry and very sweet examples do exist.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Moonlight Blossom, White Winter Cyser, Rabbit&rsquo;s Foot Apple Cyser.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MAY specify the varieties of apple used; if specified, a varietal character will be expected. Products with a relatively low proportion of honey are better entered as a Specialty Cider. A spiced cyser should be entered as a Fruit and Spice Mead. A cyser with other fruit should be entered as a Melomel. A cyser with additional ingredients should be entered as an Experimental mead.');
INSERT INTO `baseline_styles` (`id`, `brewStyleGroup`, `brewStyleNum`, `brewStyle`, `brewStyleCategory`, `brewStyleVersion`, `brewStyleOG`, `brewStyleOGMax`, `brewStyleFG`, `brewStyleFGMax`, `brewStyleABV`, `brewStyleABVMax`, `brewStyleIBU`, `brewStyleIBUMax`, `brewStyleSRM`, `brewStyleSRMMax`, `brewStyleType`, `brewStyleInfo`, `brewStyleLink`, `brewStyleActive`, `brewStyleOwn`, `brewStyleReqSpec`, `brewStyleStrength`, `brewStyleCarb`, `brewStyleSweet`, `brewStyleTags`, `brewStyleComEx`, `brewStyleEntry`) VALUES
(738, '19', '05', 'Pyment [BJCP M2B]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'In well-made examples of the style, the grape is both distinctively vinous and well-incorporated into the honey-sweet-acid-tannin-alcohol balance of the mead. White and red versions can be quite different, and the overall impression should be characteristic of the type of grapes used and suggestive of a similar variety wine. There should be an appealing blend of the fruit and honey character but not necessarily an even balance. Generally a good tannin-sweetness balance is desired, though very dry and very sweet examples do exist.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Celestial Meads Que Syrah, Moonlight Slow Dance, Redstone Pinot Noir and White Pyment Mountain Honey Wines.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MAY specify the varieties of grape used; if specified, a varietal character will be expected. A spiced pyment (hippocras) should be entered as a Fruit and Spice Mead. A pyment made with other fruit should be entered as a Melomel. A pyment with other ingredients should be entered as an Experimental Mead. '),
(739, '19', '06', 'Berry Mead [BJCP M2C]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'In well-made examples of the style, the fruit is both distinctive and well-incorporated into the honey-sweet-acid-tannin-alcohol balance of the mead. Different types of fruit can result in widely different characteristics; allow for a variation in the final product.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Moonlight Blissful, Wild, Caress, and Mischief, White Winter Blueberry, Raspberry and Strawberry Melomels, Celestial Meads Miel Noir, Redstone Black Raspberry Nectar, Bees Brothers Raspberry Mead, Intermiel Honey Wine and Raspberries, Honey Wine and Blueberries, and Honey Wine and Blackcurrants, Mountain Meadows Cranberry Mead.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MUST specify the varieties of fruit used. A mead made with both berries and non-berry fruit (including apples and grapes) should be entered as a Melomel. A berry mead that is spiced should be entered as a Fruit and Spice Mead. A berry mead containing other ingredients should be entered as an Experimental Mead.'),
(740, '19', '07', 'Stone Fruit Mead [BJCP M2D]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'In well-made examples of the style, the fruit is both distinctive and well-incorporated into the honey-sweet-acid-tannin-alcohol balance of the mead. Different types of fruit can result in widely different characteristics; allow for a variation in the final product.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Mountain Meadows Cherry Mead, Moonlight Entice, Sumptuous, Flirt, and Smitten, Redstone Sunshine Nectar.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MUST specify the varieties of fruit used. A stone fruit mead that is spiced should be entered as a Fruit and Spice Mead. A stone fruit mead that contains non-stone fruit should be entered as a Melomel. A stone fruit mead that contains other ingredients should be entered as an Experimental Mead.'),
(741, '19', '08', 'Melomel [BJCP M2E]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'In well-made examples of the style, the fruit is both distinctive and well-incorporated into the honey-sweet-acid-tannin-alcohol balance of the mead. Different types of fruit can result in widely different characteristics; allow for a variation in the final product.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Moonlight Desire, Paramour, and Iniquity.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MUST specify the varieties of fruit used. A melomel that is spiced should be entered as a Fruit and Spice Mead. A melomel containing other ingredients should be entered as an Experimental Mead. Melomels made with either apples or grapes as the only fruit source should be entered as Cysers and Pyments, respectively. Melomels with apples or grapes, plus other fruit should be entered in this category, not Experimental.'),
(742, '19', '09', 'Fruit and Spice Mead [BJCP M3A]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'In well-made examples of the style, the fruits and spices are both distinctive and well-incorporated into the honey-sweet-acid-tannin-alcohol balance of the mead. Different types of fruits and spices can result in widely different characteristics; allow for significant variation in the final product.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Moonlight Kurt&rsquo;s Apple Pie, Mojo, Flame, Fling, and Deviant, Celestial Meads Scheherazade, Rabbit\'s Foot Private Reserve Pear Mead, Intermiel Rosee.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MUST specify the types of spices used, (although well-known spice blends may be referred to by common name, such as apple pie spices). Entrants MUST specify the types of fruits used. If only combinations of spices are used, enter as a Spice, Herb, or Vegetable Mead. If only combinations of fruits are used, enter as a Melomel. If other types of ingredients are used, enter as an Experimental Mead.'),
(743, '19', '10', 'Spice, Herb, or Vegetable Mead [BJCP M3B]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'In well-made examples of the style, the spices are both distinctive and well-incorporated into the honey-sweet-acid-tannin-alcohol balance of the mead. Different types of spices can result in widely different characteristics; allow for a variation in the final product. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Moonlight Wicked, Breathless, Madagascar, and Seduction, Redstone Vanilla Beans and Cinnamon Sticks Mountain Honey Wine, Bonair Chili.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MUST specify the types of spices used (although well-known spice blends may be referred to by common name, such as apple pie spices)'),
(744, '19', '11', 'Braggot [BJCP M4A]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'A harmonious blend of mead and beer, with the distinctive characteristics of both. A wide range of results are possible, depending on the base style of beer, variety of honey and overall sweetness and strength. Beer flavors tend to somewhat mask typical honey flavors found in other meads. and honey, although the specific balance is open to creative interpretation by brewers.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Rabbit\'s Foot Diabhal and Biere de Miele, Magic Hat Braggot, Brother Adams Braggot Barleywine Ale, White Winter Traditional Brackett.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MAY specify the base style or beer or types of malt used. Products with a relatively low proportion of honey should be entered in the Spiced Beer category as a Honey Beer.'),
(745, '19', '12', 'Historical Mead [BJCP M4B]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'This mead should exhibit the character of all of the ingredients in varying degrees, and should show a good blending or balance between the various flavor elements. Whatever ingredients are included, the result should be identifiable as a honey-based fermented beverage.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Jadwiga, Saba Tej.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MUST specify the special nature of the mead, providing a description of the mead for judges if no such description is available from the BJCP.'),
(746, '19', '13', 'Experimental Mead [BJCP M4C]', 'Mead', 'AABC2022', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '3', 'This mead should exhibit the character of all of the ingredients in varying degrees, and should show a good blending or balance between the various flavor elements. Whatever ingredients are included, the result should be identifiable as a honey-based fermented beverage.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Moonlight Utopian, Hanssens/Lurgashall Mead the Gueuze, White Winter Cherry Bracket, Mountain Meadows Trickster&rsquo;s Treat Agave Mead.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level, strength, and sweetness. Entrants MAY specify honey varieties. Entrants MUST specify the special nature of the mead, whether it is a combination of existing styles, an experimental mead, or some other creation. Any special ingredients that impart an identifiable character MAY be declared.'),
(747, '20', '01', 'New World Cider [BJCP C1A]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.045', '1.065', '0.995', '1.02', '5', '8', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'A refreshing drink of some substance - not bland or watery. Sweet ciders MUST not be cloying. Dry ciders MUST not be too austere. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '[US] Uncle John&rsquo;s Fruit House Winery Apple Hard Cider, Tandem Ciders Pretty Penny (MI), Bellwether Spyglass (NY), West County Pippin (MA), White Winter Hard Apple Cider (WI), Wandering Aengus Ciderworks Bloom (OR), &Aelig;ppeltreow Appely Brut and Doux (WI).', NULL),
(748, '20', '02', 'English Cider [BJCP C1B]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.05', '1.075', '0.995', '1.015', '6', '9', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'Generally dry, full-bodied, austere. Complex flavor profile, long finish.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '[US] Westcott Bay Traditional Very Dry, Dry and Medium Sweet (WA), Farnum Hill Extra-Dry, Dry, and Farmhouse (NH), Wandering Aengus Dry Cider (OR), Montana CiderWorks North Fork (MT), Bellwether Heritage (NY). [UK] Oliver&rsquo;s Traditional Dry, Hogan&rsquo;s Dry and Medium Dry, Henney&rsquo;s Dry and Vintage Still, Burrow Hill Medium, Aspall English Imperial.', NULL),
(749, '20', '03', 'French Cider [BJCP C1C]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.05', '1.065', '1.01', '1.02', '3', '6', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'Medium to sweet, full-bodied, rich.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '[US] West County Reine de Pomme (MA), [France] Eric Bordelet (various), Etienne Dupont, Etienne Dupont Organic, Bellot.', NULL),
(750, '20', '04', 'New World Perry [BJCP C1D]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.05', '1.06', '1', '1.02', '5', '7', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'Mild. Medium to medium-sweet. Still to lightly sparkling. Only very slight acetification is acceptable. Mousiness, ropy/oily characters are serious faults.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '[US] White Winter Hard Pear Cider (WI), Uncle John&rsquo;s Fruit House Winery Perry (MI).', NULL),
(751, '20', '05', 'Traditional Perry [BJCP C1E]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.05', '1.07', '1', '1.02', '5', '9', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'Tannic. Medium to medium-sweet. Still to lightly sparkling. Only very slight acetification is acceptable. Mousiness and ropy/oily characters are serious faults.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 1, 1, '', '[US] Appeltreow Orchard Oriole Perry (WI); [France] Bordelet Poire Authentique and Poire Granit, Christian Drouin Poire, [UK] Oliver&rsquo;s Classic, Blakeney Red, and Herefordshire Dry; Hogan&rsquo;s Vintage Perry.', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level (3 levels). Entrants MUST specify sweetness (5 categories). Entrants MUST state variety of pear(s) used.'),
(752, '20', '06', 'New England Cider [BJCP C2A]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.06', '1.1', '0.995', '1.02', '7', '13', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'Substantial body and character. Typically relatively dry, but can be somewhat sweet if in balance and not containing hot alcohol.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 1, 1, '', '[US] Snowdrift Semi-Dry (WA), Blackbird Cider Works New England Style (NY).', 'Entrants MUST specify if the cider was barrel-fermented or aged. Entrants MUST specify carbonation level (3 levels). Entrants MUST specify sweetness (5 levels).'),
(753, '20', '07', 'Cider with Other Fruit [BJCP C2B]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.045', '1.07', '0.995', '1.01', '5', '9', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'Substantial. May be significantly tannic, depending on fruit added.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 1, 1, '', '[US] West County Blueberry-Apple Wine (MA), Bellwether Cherry Street (NY), Uncle John&rsquo;s Fruit Farm Winery Apple Cherry, Apple Blueberry, and Apricot Apple Hard Cider (MI).', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level (3 levels). Entrants MUST specify sweetness (5 categories). Entrants MUST specify all fruit(s) and/or fruit juice(s) added.'),
(754, '20', '08', 'Applewine [BJCP C2C]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.07', '1.1', '0.995', '1.02', '9', '12', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'Typically like a dry white wine, balanced, and with low astringency and bitterness. ', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '[US] Uncle John\'s Fruit House Winery Fruit House Apple (MI), McClure&rsquo;s Sweet Apple Wine (IN).', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level (3 levels). Entrants MUST specify sweetness (5 levels).'),
(755, '20', '09', 'Ice Cider [BJCP C2D]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.13', '1.18', '1.06', '1.085', '7', '13', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'This is a cider style in which the juice is concentrated before fermentation either by freezing fruit before pressing or freezing juice and removing water.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 1, 0, '', '[US] various from Eden Ice Cider Company and Champlain Orchards. [Canada] Domaine Pinnacle, Les Vergers de la Colline, and Cidrerie St-Nicolas (Quebec).', 'Entrants MUST specify starting gravity, final gravity or residual sugar, and alcohol level. Entrants MUST specify carbonation level (3 levels).'),
(756, '20', '10', 'Cider with Herbs/Spices [BJCP C2E]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.045', '1.07', '0.995', '1.01', '5', '9', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'Like a white wine with complex flavors. The apple character MUST marry with the botanicals and give a balanced result.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 1, 1, '', '[US] Colorado Cider Grasshop-ah (CO), Wandering Aengus Anthem Hops (OR).', 'Entrants MUST specify carbonation level (3 levels). Entrants MUST specify sweetness (5 categories). Entrants MUST specify all botanicals added. If hops are used, entrant MUST specify variety/varieties used.'),
(757, '20', '11', 'Specialty Cider/Perry [BJCP C2F]', 'Cider & Perry', 'AABC2022', '1.045', '1.1', '0.995', '1.02', '5', '12', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '2', 'This is an open-ended category for cider or perry with other ingredients such that it does not fit any of the other BJCP categories.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, 0, 1, 1, '', NULL, 'Entrants MUST specify all ingredients. Entrants MUST specify carbonation level (3 levels). Entrants MUST specify sweetness (5 categories).'),
(758, 'C1', 'A', 'Low-Tannin Ciders Dry', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider made from fermenting apples. Exhibits characteristics of ciders commonly made from low tannin apples (formerly listed as dessert or culinary). Low tannin ciders may be higher in acidity. High tannin characters, such as heavy astringency or associated mouthfeel should not be notably present. FG &#60; 1.007 (&#60; 1.8 Brix).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong> specify ABV.</p>'),
(759, 'C1', 'B', 'Low-Tannin Ciders Sweet', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider made from fermenting apples. Exhibits characteristics of ciders commonly made from low tannin apples (formerly listed as dessert or culinary). Low tannin ciders may be higher in acidity. High tannin characters, such as heavy astringency or associated mouthfeel should not be notably present. FG &#62; 1.007 (&#62; 1.8 Brix).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p>'),
(760, 'C2', 'A', 'High-Tannin Ciders Dry', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider made from fermenting apples. Exhibits characteristics of ciders commonly made from high tannin apples (i.e. bittersweet/bittersharp, formerly listed as heirloom or cider apples). May include wild or crab apples. Tannins and some astringency should be present. Sweetness, acid and tannins should be in harmony. FG &#60; 1.007 (&#60; 1.8 Brix).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p>'),
(761, 'C2', 'B', 'High-Tannin Ciders Sweet', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider made from fermenting apples. Exhibits characteristics of ciders commonly made from high tannin apples (i.e. bittersweet/bittersharp, formerly listed as heirloom or cider apples). May include wild or crab apples. Tannins and some astringency should be present. Sweetness, acid and tannins should be in harmony. FG &#62; 1.007 (&#62; 1.8 Brix).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p>'),
(762, 'C3', 'A', 'Red-Fleshed Ciders Dry', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider made from fermenting apples. Ciders whose color is derived entirely from red-fleshed and/or red-skinned apples (i.e. Mountain Rose, Airlie Redflesh, Redfield, Cranberry, Dolgo, Geneva Crab, Niedzwetzkyana, Pink Pearl). May have a blend of non-red fleshed apples and red fleshed apples. Ciders whose color is derived in whole or in part from added ingredients (blueberries, grape skins, rose petals, etc.) should be entered in Fruit or Botanical. FG &#60; 1.007 (&#60; 1.8 Brix).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify apples used.</p>'),
(763, 'C3', 'B', 'Red-Fleshed Ciders Sweet', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider made from fermenting apples. Ciders whose color is derived entirely from red-fleshed and/or red-skinned apples (i.e. Mountain Rose, Airlie Redflesh, Redfield, Cranberry, Dolgo, Geneva Crab, Niedzwetzkyana, Pink Pearl). May have a blend of non-red fleshed apples and red fleshed apples. Ciders whose color is derived in whole or in part from added ingredients (blueberries, grape skins, rose petals, etc.) should be entered in Fruit or Botanical. FG &#62; 1.007 (&#62; 1.8 Brix).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify apples used.</p>'),
(764, 'C4', 'A', 'Low-Tannin Perries', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Made from pears, not apples and without apple additions. Typically crafted from perry pears, grown specifically for fermentation rather than eating.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MAY</u></strong>  specify pears used.</p>'),
(765, 'C4', 'B', 'High-Tannin Perries', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Made from pears, not apples and without apple additions. Typically crafted from perry pears, grown specifically for fermentation rather than eating.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MAY</u></strong>  specify pears used.</p>'),
(766, 'C5', 'A', 'Wood/Oaked', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Ciders must exhibit some flavors or aromas of wood aging. Wood and oak flavors should complement the base cider.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify wood used, including the type of wine, beer or spirits barrel, if applicable.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MAY</u></strong>  specify apples and process used.</p>'),
(767, 'C6', 'A', 'Single Varietal ', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider made from a single apple variety or perry made from a single pear variety.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify apple or pear variety used.</p>'),
(768, 'C7', 'A', 'Fruit Co-Fermented', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Co-Fermented Ciders are made from apples fermented with other fruit(s). Co-Fermented Perries are made from pears fermented with other fruit(s).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify all fruits used.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify primary fruit.</p>'),
(769, 'C7', 'B', 'Fruit Post-Fermentation Addition Sweet', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Post Fermentation ciders and perries have other fruit(s) added after fermentation. FG > 1.007 (> 1.8 Brix).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify all fruits used.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify primary fruit. FG > 1.007 (> 1.8 Brix).</p>'),
(770, 'C7', 'C', 'Fruit Post-Fermentation Addition Dry', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Post Fermentation ciders and perries have other fruit(s) added after fermentation. FG < 1.007 (< 1.8 Brix).', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong> specify all fruits used.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong> specify primary fruit. FG < 1.007 (< 1.8 Brix).</p>'),
(771, 'C8', 'A', 'Botanical Hopped ', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider or perry with the addition of hops.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify hop variety or varieties.</p><p>Entrants MAY specify apples or pears used.</p>'),
(772, 'C8', 'B', 'Botanical Herbed', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider or perry made with herbs. For the competition purposes, Herbs typically refer to the leafy, fresh part of a plant. Examples of herbs include: basil, lemongrass, lavender, mint, and rosemary. Herbs used must be in balance and the flavor of cider or perry must be present.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify herbs and and/or spices used.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MAY</u></strong>  specify apples or pears used.</p>'),
(773, 'C8', 'C', 'Botanical Spiced', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Cider or perry made with spices. For competition purposes, spices refers to the root, stem, seed, fruit, flower or bark of the tree or plant (often dried not fresh). Examples of spices: cardamom, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, nutmeg, pepper, turmeric, ginger, mace, saffron, vanilla, black pepper. Spices used must be in balance and the flavor of cider or perry must be present.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify spices and/or herbs used.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MAY</u></strong>  specify apples or pears used.</p>'),
(774, 'C9', 'A', 'Specialty Fortified ', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Fortified Cider is cider that has been strengthened in alcohol either before or after fermentation, including by the addition of spirits. Fortified Cider encompasses pommeau, products made in a style similar to pommeau, and other products that emulate fortified wine styles such as apple wine and vermouth made with a base of apples and/or pears.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong> specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify the process used.</p><p>Entrants MAY specify apples or pears used.</p>'),
(775, 'C9', 'B', 'Specialty Low Alcohol/Alcohol Removed', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, '0.5', '4.5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'Low ABV ciders may be made with different processes, including rehydration of apple pomace for pressing and fermenting. Ciders that have been fermented and have alcohol removed will be expected to have some complexity beyond that of fresh juice. ABV range: 0.5% - 4.5%.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify process used (i.e., alcohol removed or ciderkin production).</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MAY</u></strong>  specify apples or pears used.</p><p>ABV range: 0.5% - 4.5%.</p>'),
(776, 'C9', 'C', 'Specialty Other', 'Cider', 'NWCiderCup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 'A cider or perry not suitable for any other category. Made with a variety of process techniques or international cider making techniques.', NULL, 'N', 'bcoe', 1, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, '<p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong> specify ABV.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong>  specify processes and ingredients that make the cider not suitable for any other category.</p><p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong> specify commercial yeast cultures or wild yeast processes (i.e., wild ferment, brettanomyces, or lactobacillus). <p>Entrants <strong><u>MUST</u></strong> note additions such as added sweeteners (i.e., honey or molasses).</p><p>Entrants MAY specify apples or pears used.</p>'),
(777, '03', '184', 'West Coast-Style India Pale Ale', 'North American Origin Ales', 'BA', '1.055', '1.070', '1.005', '1.016', '6.3', '7.5', '50', '75', '11', '20', '1', 'These beers are highly attenuated with an assertive hop character and a dry, crisp finish. While the West Coast India Pale Ale style has been around for some time, the style itself has progressed over time from original inception to modern day examples – this guideline serves to align directly with modern-day examples of the style.', 'https://www.brewersassociation.org/resources/brewers-association-beer-style-guidelines/', 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, '2023', NULL, NULL),
(778, '11', '185', 'Dessert Stout or Pastry Stout', 'Hybrid/Mixed Lagers or Ales', 'BA', '1.080', '1.120', '1.020', '1.060', '7', '13', '20', '65', '35', '50', '1', 'Beers in this category build on a strong dark beer base and incorporate culinary ingredients to create rich, sweet flavor profiles mimicking the character of desserts, pastries or candies. Examples of culinary ingredients used in these beers include, but are not limited to, chocolate, coffee, coconut, vanilla, maple syrup, peanut butter and marshmallow as well as fruits, nuts and spices. The addition of sugars from any source may contribute to the pronounced sweetness of these beers. While this category may overlap several other styles defined in these guidelines such as Chocolate or Cocoa Beers, Coffee Beers, Field beers, and others, the combination of a dark beer base, elevated alcohol content and rich, sweet, dessert-like flavor profiles sets this style apart as a unique entity.', 'https://www.brewersassociation.org/resources/brewers-association-beer-style-guidelines/', 'N', 'bcoe', 0, 0, 0, 0, '2023', NULL, NULL);

